{"type":"message","id":"b7e72920","parentId":"04ab1022","timestamp":"2026-04-03T01:55:50.813Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The runtime system event at the top says Ideator completed and generated 5 idea candidates. Let me check if the file exists and notify the user.\n","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Ideator 已回报完成。让我确认产出并通知用户选择。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_2Mn6T9NEPQt663FxHxLZ73","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/ideas/idea_candidates.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"claude-proxy","model":"claude-opus-4-6","usage":{"input":63629,"output":118,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":63747,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775181344313}}
{"type":"message","id":"ad11fcca","parentId":"b7e72920","timestamp":"2026-04-03T01:55:50.818Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_2Mn6T9NEPQt663FxHxLZ73","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 5 Research Idea Candidates for Multimodal Large Language Models in Intelligent Fault Diagnosis\n\n## Idea 1\n### Title\nIndustrialMM-LLM: Domain-Adaptive Multimodal Large Language Model for Zero-Shot Fault Diagnosis in Rotating Machinery\n\n### Core Innovation Points\nDevelops a specialized MLLM pretrained on industrial vibration signals, thermal images, and textual maintenance logs to enable zero-shot fault diagnosis without fine-tuning. Introduces a cross-modal tokenizer for vibration data integration into the LLM backbone, enhancing alignment between modalities. Leverages instruction tuning on synthetic fault scenarios for robust generalization to unseen equipment.\n\n### Technical Route Overview\n1. Curate and preprocess industrial multimodal dataset (vibration spectrograms, images, logs).  \n2. Design vibration tokenizer and fuse with vision-language encoder (e.g., CLIP-like + LLM).  \n3. Pretrain with masked multimodal modeling and contrastive learning; fine-tune via instruction-following.  \n4. Evaluate zero/few-shot performance on public/private industrial benchmarks.\n\n### Expected Contributions\n- First open-source industrial MLLM achieving superior zero-shot fault diagnosis accuracy.  \n- Large-scale multimodal industrial fault dataset for community use.  \n- Standardized evaluation protocol for MLLMs in fault diagnosis.  \n- Demonstrated 20-30% performance gains over unimodal baselines.\n\n### Feasibility Assessment\nHigh (leverages existing MLLM frameworks like LLaVA; data from public sources augmentable).\n\n### Novelty Assessment\nHigh (domain-specific pretraining for industrial multimodal fault diagnosis is underexplored).\n\n## Idea 2\n### Title\nRobustMLLM-Diag: Adaptive Cross-Modal Imputation and Fusion in Multimodal Large Language Models for Noisy Fault Diagnosis\n\n### Core Innovation Points\nProposes an adaptive fusion mechanism in MLLMs that dynamically imputes missing modalities via cross-modal retrieval and denoising using VLM components. Employs uncertainty-aware attention to weigh noisy industrial data streams (e.g., vibration under interference). Enables reliable diagnosis in real-world scenarios with 20-50% modality dropout or noise.\n\n### Technical Route Overview\n1. Build modality-specific encoders with uncertainty estimation (e.g., Bayesian dropout).  \n2. Integrate retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) for cross-modal imputation within LLM prompts.  \n3. Train end-to-end with simulated noise/missing data; use RL for robustness optimization.  \n4. Validate on augmented industrial datasets with controlled noise levels.\n\n### Expected Contributions\n- Novel adaptive imputation module improving robustness by 25% in noisy settings.  \n- Empirical analysis of MLLM failure modes in incomplete multimodal data.  \n- Toolkit for simulating industrial data corruptions.  \n- Benchmark results showing state-of-the-art resilience.\n\n### Feasibility Assessment\nHigh (builds on established RAG and uncertainty techniques; feasible with moderate compute).\n\n### Novelty Assessment\nHigh (addresses critical gap in cross-modal noise handling for industrial MLLMs).\n\n## Idea 3\n### Title\nMMFD-Bench: A Standardized Benchmark Suite with Baseline Multimodal LLM for Industrial Fault Diagnosis\n\n### Core Innovation Points\nIntroduces the first comprehensive benchmark for MLLMs in fault diagnosis, covering vibration-image-text fusion across 10+ machinery types. Provides a strong baseline MLLM fine-tuned on the benchmark data, supporting zero/few-shot and noisy evaluations. Includes real-world deployment metrics like inference latency.\n\n### Technical Route Overview\n1. Collect/annotate multimodal dataset from diverse industrial sources (e.g., Case Western, Paderborn).  \n2. Design benchmark tasks: diagnosis, severity estimation, root-cause localization.  \n3. Fine-tune open MLLMs (e.g., LLaVA-Med variant) as baseline; evaluate 5+ SOTA models.  \n4. Open-source benchmark with leaderboards and edge deployment scripts.\n\n### Expected Contributions\n- MMFD-Bench: New standard dataset/tasks for MLLM fault diagnosis research.  \n- Baseline model outperforming traditional ML by 15-20%.  \n- Insights into MLLM scaling laws for fault diagnosis.  \n- Facilitates reproducible comparisons in the community.\n\n### Feasibility Assessment\nMedium (data curation intensive but feasible via public datasets + labeling tools).\n\n### Novelty Assessment\nHigh (no existing standardized multimodal LLM benchmark for fault diagnosis).\n\n## Idea 4\n### Title\nCausalMM-LLM: Physics-Guided Multimodal Large Language Model for Interpretable Fault Reasoning and Diagnosis\n\n### Core Innovation Points\nInfuses physical domain knowledge (e.g., machinery dynamics equations) into MLLM prompts and fine-tuning to generate causal fault graphs. Enhances interpretability via attention visualization and counterfactual reasoning for safety-critical decisions. Achieves traceable diagnosis chains explaining vibration-image discrepancies.\n\n### Technical Route Overview\n1. Embed physics simulators (e.g., ODE-based fault models) for synthetic data generation.  \n2. Fine-tune MLLM with physics-constrained prompts and causal chain-of-thought.  \n3. Develop visualization tools for causal graphs from LLM outputs.  \n4. Test interpretability via human expert validation and ablation studies.\n\n### Expected Contributions\n- Interpretable causal reasoning framework boosting trust in MLLM diagnosis.  \n- Physics-augmented dataset for causal fault learning.  \n- Quantitative interpretability metrics (e.g., faithfulness scores).  \n- 10-15% accuracy gain with full explainability.\n\n### Feasibility Assessment\nHigh (prompt engineering + fine-tuning; physics libs readily available).\n\n### Novelty Assessment\nHigh (first physics-informed causal reasoning in multimodal fault LLMs).\n\n## Idea 5\n### Title\nEdgeMM-LLM: Hybrid Distilled Multimodal Large Language Model for Real-Time Fault Diagnosis on Industrial Edge Devices\n\n### Core Innovation Points\nDistills heavy MLLM into a hybrid LLM-lightweight Transformer for edge deployment, maintaining multimodal fusion with &lt;1s inference. Uses knowledge distillation from teacher MLLM and modality pruning for efficiency. Supports real-time streaming diagnosis from IoT sensors.\n\n### Technical Route Overview\n1. Train teacher MLLM on industrial data; distill to student hybrid model.  \n2. Optimize with quantization, pruning, and efficient attention (e.g., FlashAttention).  \n3. Deploy on edge hardware (e.g., Jetson); evaluate latency/accuracy trade-offs.  \n4. Field-test in simulated industrial environments.\n\n### Expected Contributions\n- First edge-deployable MLLM for multimodal fault diagnosis (&lt;500MB, &lt;100ms inference).  \n- Distillation framework reducing parameters by 90% with minimal accuracy loss.  \n- Real-world deployment case study on rotating machinery.  \n- Guidelines for scaling MLLMs to industrial IoT.\n\n### Feasibility Assessment\nMedium (distillation compute-heavy; edge hardware access needed).\n\n### Novelty Assessment\nHigh (bridges gap in scalable, real-time MLLM edge inference for diagnosis).\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775181350817}}
{"type":"message","id":"f4b5998c","parentId":"ad11fcca","timestamp":"2026-04-03T01:55:59.745Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Ideator 完成，5 个创意候选：\n\n1. **IndustrialMM-LLM** — 工业领域自适应 MLLM，零样本故障诊断（新颖性高，可行性高）\n2. **RobustMLLM-Diag** — 噪声/缺失模态下的自适应融合与补全（新颖性高，可行性高）\n3. **MMFD-Bench** — 首个多模态 LLM 故障诊断标准化 Benchmark（新颖性高，可行性中）\n4. **CausalMM-LLM** — 物理引导的因果推理可解释故障诊断（新颖性高，可行性高）\n5. **EdgeMM-LLM** — 蒸馏轻量化 MLLM 边缘端实时诊断（新颖性高，可行性中）\n\n请选择一个 idea（或组合），我继续推进到阶段 3（Architect 框架设计）。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"claude-proxy","model":"claude-opus-4-6","usage":{"input":65690,"output":220,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65910,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775181350819}}
