{"type":"message","id":"224d49e6","parentId":"fc1a1f68","timestamp":"2026-04-03T02:56:48.449Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Need to reduce from 19 to ~12-15. I'll remove the redundant equations in Method Section D (fusion section has duplicate formulations). Let me remove Eq. fusion, crossattn (already in background), and gating (can be described in text)."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_PgCWPGLPJxkZ4lomgr4UR4","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/drafts/v2/method.tex","old_string":"The fused representation is a weighted sum augmented with cross-modal interactions:\n\\begin{equation}\nh_f = \\sum_{i} \\alpha_i \\tilde{h}_i + \\text{CrossAttn}(Q=\\tilde{h}_v, K=\\{\\tilde{h}_t, \\tilde{h}_a\\}, V=\\{\\alpha_t \\tilde{h}_t, \\alpha_a \\tilde{h}_a\\}),\n\\label{eq:fusion}\n\\end{equation}\nwhere CrossAttn follows the scaled dot-product formulation:\n\\begin{equation}\n\\text{Attention}(Q,K,V) = \\text{softmax}\\Bigl( \\frac{QK^\\top}{\\sqrt{d_k}} \\Bigr) V,\n\\label{eq:crossattn}\n\\end{equation}\nwith vibration $h_v$ as query (most reliable baseline) and others as key-value pairs scaled by $\\alpha$. This 8-head multi-head attention (head dim $d_k=96$) captures complementary fault cues (e.g., thermal hotspots aligning with vibration harmonics).","new_string":"The cross-attention mechanism in Eq.~\\eqref{eq:fusion_enhanced} follows the scaled dot-product formulation from Eq.~\\eqref{eq:attention} in Section~\\ref{sec:background}, with vibration $h_v$ as query and thermal/acoustic as key-value pairs scaled by $\\alpha$. This 8-head attention (head dim $d_k=96$) captures complementary fault cues (e.g., thermal hotspots aligning with vibration harmonics)."}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"claude-proxy","model":"claude-opus-4-6","usage":{"input":112403,"output":547,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":112950,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite"