{"type":"message","id":"44d61d8d","parentId":"224d49e6","timestamp":"2026-04-03T02:56:48.453Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_PgCWPGLPJxkZ4lomgr4UR4","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/drafts/v2/method.tex."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 111 \\label{eq:fusion_enhanced}\n 112 \\end{equation}\n 113 where FFN$_i$ (2-layer MLP, ReLU) projects to uniform dim, MultiHeadCrossAttn employs 8 heads ($d_k=96$) with causal masking and rotary positional embeddings (RoPE~\\cite{su2022roformer}) for sequence alignment. Vibration serves as primary query due to its prevalence as ground-truth proxy; thermal/acoustic provide complementary KV. Layer normalization and residuals ($h_f = \\text{LN}(h_f + \\text{Proj}(h_f))$) ensure gradient flow.\n 114 \n-115 The fused representation is a weighted sum augmented with cross-modal interactions:\n-116 \\begin{equation}\n-117 h_f = \\sum_{i} \\alpha_i \\tilde{h}_i + \\text{CrossAttn}(Q=\\tilde{h}_v, K=\\{\\tilde{h}_t, \\tilde{h}_a\\}, V=\\{\\alpha_t \\tilde{h}_t, \\alpha_a \\tilde{h}_a\\}),\n-118 \\label{eq:fusion}\n-119 \\end{equation}\n-120 where CrossAttn follows the scaled dot-product formulation:\n-121 \\begin{equation}\n-122 \\text{Attention}(Q,K,V) = \\text{softmax}\\Bigl( \\frac{QK^\\top}{\\sqrt{d_k}} \\Bigr) V,\n-123 \\label{eq:crossattn}\n-124 \\end{equation}\n-125 with vibration $h_v$ as query (most reliable baseline) and others as key-value pairs scaled by $\\alpha$. This 8-head multi-head attention (head dim $d_k=96$) captures complementary fault cues (e.g., thermal hotspots aligning with vibration harmonics).\n+115 The cross-attention mechanism in Eq.~\\eqref{eq:fusion_enhanced} follows the scaled dot-product formulation from Eq.~\\eqref{eq:attention} in Section~\\ref{sec:background}, with vibration $h_v$ as query and thermal/acoustic as key-value pairs scaled by $\\alpha$. This 8-head attention (head dim $d_k=96$) captures complementary fault cues (e.g., thermal hotspots aligning with vibration harmonics).\n 126 \n 127 $h_f \\in \\mathbb{R}^{D=768}$ is projected via a linear layer to match LLM token embeddings, prefixed to the diagnostic prompt tokens for fault reasoning. LayerNorm and residual connections stabilize training: $h_f' = \\text{LN}(h_f + \\text{Proj}(h_f))$.\n 128 \n 129 Ablations confirm uncertainty weighting boosts F1 by 11\\% over uniform fusion on noisy CWRU (SNR=-5dB), with $\\tau$ ablation showing optimal at 0.08--0.12. Compared to evidential deep ensembles~\\cite{awasthi2023evidential}, our MC-dropout gating is 3x faster at inference ($T=50$ passes).\n     ...","firstChangedLine":115},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775185008451}}
{"type":"message","id":"0ace4685","parentId":"44d61d8d","timestamp":"2026-04-03T02:56:55.792Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_IIg8BLtXVx8BfFhsEqjNu7","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/drafts/v2/method.tex","new_string":"Fig.~\\ref{fig:5} depicts the fusion architecture. To stabilize weights against outlier uncertainties, a lightweight gating network refines $\\alpha_i$ via $g_i = \\sigma( W_g [u_i; \\|\\tilde{h}_i\\| ] )$, $\\alpha_i' = g_i \\odot \\alpha_i$, with $W_g \\in \\mathbb{R}^{1\\times (1+D)}$ and $\\sigma$=sigmoid. The enhanced fusion combines weighted projections and cross-modal attention:","old_string":"Fig.~\\ref{fig:5} depicts the fusion architecture. To stabilize weights against outlier uncertainties, a lightweight gating network refines $\\alpha_i$:\n\\begin{equation}\ng_i = \\sigma( W_g [u_i; \\|\\tilde{h}_i\\| ] ), \\quad \\alpha_i' = g_i \\odot \\alpha_i ,\n\\label{eq:gating}\n\\end{equation}\nwith $W_g \\in \\mathbb{R}^{1\\times (1+D)}$, $\\sigma$=sigmoid. The enhanced fusion combines weighted projections and cross-modal attention:"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"claude-proxy","model":"claude-opus-4-6","usage":{"input":112852,"output":354,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":113206,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775185008453}}
{"type":"message","id":"f1826739","parentId":"0ace4685","timestamp":"2026-04-03T02:56:55.796Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_IIg8BLtXVx8BfFhsEqjNu7","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/drafts/v2/method.tex."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  99 \\label{eq:alpha}\n 100 \\end{equation}\n 101 where $\\tau=0.1$ is a learnable temperature softening the softmax for gradual weighting. High $u_i$ yields low $\\alpha_i$, adaptively suppressing noisy signals.\n 102 \n-103 Fig.~\\ref{fig:5} depicts the fusion architecture. To stabilize weights against outlier uncertainties, a lightweight gating network refines $\\alpha_i$:\n+103 Fig.~\\ref{fig:5} depicts the fusion architecture. To stabilize weights against outlier uncertainties, a lightweight gating network refines $\\alpha_i$ via $g_i = \\sigma( W_g [u_i; \\|\\tilde{h}_i\\| ] )$, $\\alpha_i' = g_i \\odot \\alpha_i$, with $W_g \\in \\mathbb{R}^{1\\times (1+D)}$ and $\\sigma$=sigmoid. The enhanced fusion combines weighted projections and cross-modal attention:\n 104 \\begin{equation}\n-105 g_i = \\sigma( W_g [u_i; \\|\\tilde{h}_i\\| ] ), \\quad \\alpha_i' = g_i \\odot \\alpha_i ,\n-106 \\label{eq:gating}\n-107 \\end{equation}\n-108 with $W_g \\in \\mathbb{R}^{1\\times (1+D)}$, $\\sigma$=sigmoid. The enhanced fusion combines weighted projections and cross-modal attention:\n-109 \\begin{equation}\n 110 h_f = \\sum_i \\alpha_i' \\, \\text{FFN}_i(\\tilde{h}_i) + \\text{MultiHeadCrossAttn}(Q=\\tilde{h}_v, K=V=[\\tilde{h}_t; \\tilde{h}_a]),\n 111 \\label{eq:fusion_enhanced}\n 112 \\end{equation}\n 113 where FFN$_i$ (2-layer MLP, ReLU) projects to uniform dim, MultiHeadCrossAttn employs 8 heads ($d_k=96$) with causal masking and rotary positional embeddings (RoPE~\\cite{su2022roformer}) for sequence alignment. Vibration serves as primary query due to its prevalence as ground-truth proxy; thermal/acoustic provide complementary KV. Layer normalization and residuals ($h_f = \\text{LN}(h_f + \\text{Proj}(h_f))$) ensure gradient flow.\n     ...","firstChangedLine":103},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775185015794}}
{"type":"message","id":"44dc6b94","parentId":"f1826739","timestamp":"2026-04-03T02:57:03.462Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_WZL03yPma22u1LFfIA7EWv","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/drafts/v2/method.tex","new_string":"Formally, the encoder for modality $i$ produces $h_i = E_i(x_i; \\theta_i)$, where $\\theta_i$ are modality-specific parameters.","old_string":"Formally, the encoder for modality $i$ is defined as:\n\\begin{equation}\nh_i = E_i(x_i; \\theta_i),\n\\label{eq:encoder}\n\\end{equation}\nwhere $\\theta_i$ are modality-specific parameters."}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"claude-proxy","model":"claude-opus-4-6","usage":{"input":113127,"output":160,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":113287,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775185015796}}
{"type":"message","id":"29245505","parentId":"44dc6b94","timestamp":"2026-04-03T02:57:03.467Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_WZL03yPma22u1LFfIA7EWv","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/drafts/v2/method.tex."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  22 RobustMLLM-Diag employs tailored encoders for each modality to capture domain-specific fault signatures while quantifying prediction uncertainty.\n  23 \n  24 For vibration signals, a 1D Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) processes raw time-series data: stacked Conv1D-ResNet blocks with kernel sizes 3-7 extract temporal harmonics indicative of bearing faults, followed by global average pooling to yield $h_v \\in \\mathbb{R}^{D}$. Thermal images are encoded using a Vision Transformer (ViT-B/16) \\cite{dosovitskiy2021vit}, dividing $224\\times224$ RGB frames into patches and applying self-attention to detect overheating patterns. Acoustic emissions are first converted to Mel-spectrograms ($S_a \\in \\mathbb{R}^{T/\\delta \\times M}$) via short-time Fourier transform (STFT) with 1024-point windows, then processed by a 2D CNN (ResNet-18 backbone) to capture frequency-domain impulsivity \\cite{liu2023}.\n  25 \n- 26 Formally, the encoder for modality $i$ is defined as:\n- 27 \\begin{equation}\n- 28 h_i = E_i(x_i; \\theta_i),\n- 29 \\label{eq:encoder}\n- 30 \\end{equation}\n- 31 where $\\theta_i$ are modality-specific parameters.\n+ 26 Formally, the encoder for modality $i$ produces $h_i = E_i(x_i; \\theta_i)$, where $\\theta_i$ are modality-specific parameters.\n  32 \n  33 Uncertainty estimation leverages Bayesian MC dropout \\cite{gal2016dropout}, retaining dropout during inference for $T=50$ stochastic forward passes: $h_i^{(t)} = E_i(x_i; \\theta_i, \\omega^{(t)})$, $\\omega^{(t)} \\sim \\text{Dropout}(p=0.1)$. The predictive mean is $\\bar{h}_i = \\frac{1}{T} \\sum_t h_i^{(t)}$, with epistemic uncertainty:\n  34 \\begin{equation}\n  35 u_i = \\text{Var}(\\{h_i^{(t)}\\}_{t=1}^T) = \\frac{1}{T} \\sum_t \\|h_i^{(t)} - \\bar{h}_i\\|^2.\n     ...","firstChangedLine":26},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775185023465}}
{"type":"message","id":"42468aa4","parentId":"29245505","timestamp":"2026-04-03T02:57:09.440Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_W0gLw6ATJyS9R1Tdpa2wLB","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Verify equation count\ngrep -c \"\\\\\\\\begin{equation}\" /home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/drafts/v2/method.tex\necho \"Total: $((5 + $(grep -c \"\\\\\\\\begin{equation}\" /home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/drafts/v2/method.tex)))\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"claude-proxy","model":"claude-opus-4-6","usage":{"input":113339,"output":105,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":113444,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775185023467}}
