{"type":"message","id":"a283fef2","parentId":"759e6a60","timestamp":"2026-04-03T05:25:55.332Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to redo stages 4.6 (polish) and 4.7 (de-AI) properly. I need to be very careful this time - the issue before was Writer truncating content during polish. Let me use a different approach:\n\n1. For 4.6 polish: I'll send the task with strict word count constraints and require diff-style changes only\n2. For 4.7 de-AI: Similar strict constraints\n\nActually, the better approach based on P8/P9 lessons is to handle this section by section with very tight constraints, or better yet, to do it myself as Leader since the Writer consistently fails at polish tasks.\n\nLet me try a different strategy: send very specific instructions that the Writer should ONLY make minor word/phrase changes, not rewrite paragraphs. Or I could just do it myself as Leader.\n\n\nI'll go with the section-by-section approach to keep Writer's context manageable, but I need to include an explicit truncation prevention instruction in the prompt so it doesn't accidentally cut content during the polish and de-AI stages.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"好，重新走。这次我逐 section 派发，每次只改一个文件，严格控制不截短。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_5d07ae9720aa4948b5a41d17","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Recreate v3 fresh from v2\nSHARED=\"/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9\"\nrm -rf \"$SHARED/drafts/v3\"\nmkdir -p \"$SHARED/drafts/v3\"\ncp \"$SHARED/drafts/v2/\"* \"$SHARED/drafts/v3/\"\necho \"v3 reset from v2\"\nfor f in \"$SHARED\"/drafts/v3/*.tex; do\n  echo \"  $(basename $f): $(wc -w < $f)w\"\ndone","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"xiaomi/mimo-v2-pro","usage":{"input":670,"output":617,"cacheRead":111680,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":112967,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":17751939