historical data using multimodal prompts; (2) an uncertainty-aware attention mechanism leveraging Bayesian Monte Carlo dropout for epistemic uncertainty quantification and dynamic modality weighting during fusion; (3) an end-to-end training strategy augmented with Proximal Policy Optimization (PPO) reinforcement learning to refine diagnostic policies under simulated noise and dropout perturbations; and (4) rigorous empirical validation on the CWRU and Paderborn benchmarks, demonstrating superior accuracy (96.2\\% on CWRU clean, 91.3\\% noisy) and robustness, outperforming existing baselines by over 15\\% across 20-50\\% noise and missing modality scenarios.","cwd":"/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/leader/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775194800528}}
