{"type":"message","id":"74346fff","parentId":"05fba4a3","timestamp":"2026-04-03T05:47:39.948Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There are many issues:1. Undefined citations - the \\cite keys don't match the bib entries. This is because some cite keys in the section files use different names than in references.bib.2. Undefined label references - some \\ref{} references to figures and tables that don't exist.3. Undefined control sequences - possibly \\IEEEPARstart or other IEEE commands.Let me focus on the citation issue first, which is the most critical. The bibtex needs to run on the paper.tex file, but the cite keys in the section files may not match references.bib.Actually, looking more carefully, the citations ARE in references.bib (I verified earlier that all 56 cite keys match). The issue is that bibtex ran on the first pdflatex pass, but there were warnings about some entries. Let me check if the .bbl file was generated.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6e978d5b1a004ee79213ffc8","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/final/v1/ && \\\n# Re-run the full compile cycle properly\npdflatex -interaction=nonstopmode paper.tex > /dev/null 2>&1\nbibtex paper 2>&1\npdflatex -interaction=nonstopmode paper.tex > /dev/null 2>&1\npdflatex -interaction=nonstopmode paper.tex > /dev/null 2>&1\necho \"=== Undefined citations remaining ===\"\ngrep \"Citation.*undefined\" paper.log | sed 's/.*Citation `//;s/'\\''.*//' | sort -u\necho \"=== Undefined refs ===\"\ngrep \"Reference.*undefined\" paper.log | sed 's/.*Reference `//;s/'\\''.*//' | sort -u\necho \"=== Undefined control seq ===\"\ngrep \"Undefined control\" paper.log | head -5\necho \"=== PDF ===\"\nls -lh paper.pdf","timeout":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"xiaomi/mimo-v2-pro","usage":{"input":3649,"output":604,"cacheRead":130752,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":13500