{"type":"message","id":"8f805495","parentId":"6d67613f","timestamp":"2026-04-03T05:48:01.809Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so:\n- `sec:background` is not defined - background.tex has `\\section{Theoretical Background}` but no `\\label{sec:background}`. I need to add it.\n- `fig:3`, `fig:4`, `fig:5`, `fig:framework`, `fig:noise_patterns`, `fig:overview`, `fig:tsne` - these are figure references but there are no figure files. This is expected.\n- `tab:notation` is defined in background.tex - good.\n\nThe main issue is that `sec:background` label is missing. Let me fix it and add other missing labels.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_685707af727f4f4db5021a7e","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/final/v1/background.tex","old_string":"\\section{Theoretical Background}","new_string":"\\section{Theoretical Background}\n\\label{sec:background}"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"xiaomi/mimo-v2-pro","usage":{"input":722,"output":343,"cacheRead":135488,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":136553,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775195275738}}
{"type":"message","id":"aa5eda6d","parentId":"8f805495","timestamp":"2026-04-03T05:48:01.817Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_685707af727f4f4db5021a7e","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/final/v1/background.tex."}],"details":{"diff":"  1 \\section{Theoretical Background}\n+ 2 \\label{sec:background}\n  2 \n  3 Building upon the multimodal challenges and gaps in noisy fault diagnosis discussed in Section~\\ref{sec:intro}, this section outlines the key theoretical foundations of our RobustMLLM-Diag framework, as shown in Fig.~\\ref{fig:overview} (Fig. 1) and Fig.~\\ref{fig:noise_patterns} (Fig. 2). We examine multimodal large language models (MLLMs), retrieval-augmented generation (RAG), uncertainty estimation, and reinforcement learning (RL) approaches for robustness. These elements establish the basis for adaptive imputation and fusion when dealing with noise and missing data.\n  4 \n  5 \\subsection{A. Multimodal Large Language Models}\n    ...","firstChangedLine":2},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775195281812}}
