{"type":"message","id":"965666b2","parentId":"483a2889","timestamp":"2026-04-03T06:01:19.645Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"56 unique keys. I need to reduce to ≤45. That means removing 11 keys. Let me identify the least essential ones that are cited only once:- windfarm2024, steelmill2025, semicond2024, roboweld2024, rigdiag2025, chemproc2024, avimro2024, autopower2024 - these are all single-use industrial domain papers that were added to boost references- hoang2020diffusion - single use, older paper- cuturi2013sinkhorn - single use, algorithm reference- awasthi2023evidential - single useI should remove these 11 and adjust the text accordingly. \n\nRather than making these changes across the section files where they're scattered, I'll take a more direct approach by modifying the bibliography itself. I'll identify which section files contain these rarely-cited references and remove them from there, then clean up the corresponding entries in references.bib. The experiments.tex file seems like a good starting point since several of these single-use papers appear there.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"56 keys，需精简至 ≤45。删除 11 个低频单次引用的非核心文献："},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_e4b62cabf8154b8abb4b5037","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"SHARED=\"/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/final/v1\"\n# Keys to remove (all cited once, supplementary industrial papers)\nREMOVE=\"autopower2024 avimro2024 chemproc2024 hoang2020diffusion roboweld2024 rigdiag2025 semicond2024 steelmill2025 windfarm2024 scikit-learn cuturi2013sinkhorn\"\n\necho \"=== Finding locations ===\"\nfor key in $REMOVE; do\n  echo \"--- $key ---\"\n  grep -rn \"\\\\\\\\cite{.*$key\" \"$SHARED\"/*.tex paper.tex\ndone","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"xiaomi/mimo-v2-pro","usage":{"input":467,"output":700,"cacheRead":144064,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":145231,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"