{"type":"message","id":"4d959a60","parentId":"965666b2","timestamp":"2026-04-03T06:01:19.658Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_e4b62cabf8154b8abb4b5037","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== Finding locations ===\n--- autopower2024 ---\n/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/final/v1/background.tex:37:Examples from industry include semiconductor manufacturing, where RAG pipelines pull archival clean wafer scans to fill in missing acoustic emissions from plasma etching. This enables defect detection with sub-micron precision. In automotive transmission testing, retrieval from large sensor datasets imputes dropped thermal profiles using vibration logs, improving diagnostic yield by 12\\% amid real-world packet loss \\cite{semicond2024,autopower2024}.\n--- avimro2024 ---\n/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/final/v1/background.tex:51:In chemical engineering facilities, this approach adjusts uncertainty from FTIR spectra affected by steam plumes, muting unreliable channels to protect reaction monitoring. Aviation engine health management applies MC dropout to turbine vibro-acoustic data, adjusting weights against EGT drift to boost prognostics by 15\\% \\cite{chemproc2024,avimro2024}.\n--- chemproc2024 ---\n/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/final/v1/background.tex:51:In chemical engineering facilities, this approach adjusts uncertainty from FTIR spectra affected by steam plumes, muting unreliable channels to protect reaction monitoring. Aviation engine health management applies MC dropout to turbine vibro-acoustic data, adjusting weights against EGT drift to boost prognostics by 15\\% \\cite{chemproc2024,avimro2024}.\n--- hoang2020diffusion ---\n/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/final/v1/method.tex:82:This cross-modal RAG outperforms naive imputation (e.g., zero-filling, mean) by 12--18\\% in accuracy under 40\\% random modality dropout, surpassing domain-specific diffusion models~\\cite{hoang2020diffusion}. Compared to vanilla RAG~\\cite{lewis2020retrieval}, our CLIP-based retrieval achieves 25\\% higher recall@5 across heterogeneous modalities, as ablated on simulated PU data with thermal occlusion.\n--- roboweld2024 ---\n/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/final/v1/background.tex:65:Industrial robotics applications, like arc welding cells, apply PPO to adjust end-effector policies despite plasma glare in vision inputs. Offshore oil rig diagnostics use RL to address seismic distortions in drilling telemetry, increasing uptime by 22\\% with adaptive fault-handling policies \\cite{roboweld2024,rigdiag2025}.\n--- rigdiag2025 ---\n/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/final/v1/background.tex:65:Industrial robotics applications, like arc welding cells, apply PPO to adjust end-effector policies despite plasma glare in vision inputs. Offshore oil rig diagnostics use RL to address seismic distortions in drilling telemetry, increasing uptime by 22\\% with adaptive fault-handling policies \\cite{roboweld2024,rigdiag2025}.\n--- semicond2024 ---\n/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/final/v1/background.tex:37:Examples from industry include semiconductor manufacturing, where RAG pipelines pull archival clean wafer scans to fill in missing acoustic emissions from plasma etching. This enables defect detection with sub-micron precision. In automotive transmission testing, retrieval from large sensor datasets imputes dropped thermal profiles using vibration logs, improving diagnostic yield by 12\\% amid real-world packet loss \\cite{semicond2024,autopower2024}.\n--- steelmill2025 ---\n/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/final/v1/background.tex:23:In industrial settings, such as predictive maintenance for wind turbine generators, MLLMs integrate vibration spectrograms with thermal images to detect bearing wear in advance. Systems deployed on offshore wind farms, relying on CLIP-aligned embeddings, achieve 92\\% zero-shot fault localization accuracy despite challenges like salt spray and wind-induced vibrations \\cite{windfarm2024}. Similarly, in heavy machinery such as steel rolling mills, Flamingo-style cross-attention handles acoustic signals together with surface defect images. This integration reduces unplanned outages by 25\\% via early crack detection \\cite{steelmill2025}.\n--- windfarm2024 ---\n/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/final/v1/background.tex:23:In industrial settings, such as predictive maintenance for wind turbine generators, MLLMs integrate vibration spectrograms with thermal images to detect bearing wear in advance. Systems deployed on offshore wind farms, relying on CLIP-aligned embeddings, achieve 92\\% zero-shot fault localization accuracy despite challenges like salt spray and wind-induced vibrations \\cite{windfarm2024}. Similarly, in heavy machinery such as steel rolling mills, Flamingo-style cross-attention handles acoustic signals together with surface defect images. This integration reduces unplanned outages by 25\\% via early crack detection \\cite{steelmill2025}.\n--- scikit-learn ---\n/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/final/v1/experiments.tex:66:Statistical significance is assessed via paired t-tests (p<0.01) across 5 runs with different seeds. These metrics comprehensively capture diagnostic efficacy, balancing nominal performance with degradation resilience \\cite{scikit-learn}.\n--- cuturi2013sinkhorn ---\n/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/final/v1/method.tex:80:approximated efficiently with Sinkhorn-Knopp iterations~\\cite{cuturi2013sinkhorn} (20 iterations, $\\epsilon=0.01$). If $W_1 < \\delta=0.15$ (empirically tuned), $\\hat{x}_i$ is encoded to $\\hat{h}_i, \\hat{u}_i$; else, modality $i$ is masked."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":9,"aggregated":"=== Finding locations ===\n--- autopower2024 ---\n/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/final/v1/background.tex:37:Examples from industry include semiconductor manufacturing, where RAG pipelines pull archival clean wafer scans to fill in missing acoustic emissions from plasma etching. This enables defect detection with sub-micron precision. In automotive transmission testing, retrieval from large sensor datasets imputes dropped thermal profiles using vibration logs, improving diagnostic yield by 12\\% amid real-world packet loss \\cite{semicond2024,autopower2024}.\n--- avimro2024 ---\n/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/final/v1/background.tex:51:In chemical engineering facilities, this approach adjusts uncertainty from FTIR spectra affected by steam plumes, muting unreliable channels to protect reaction monitoring. Aviation engine health management applies MC dropout to turbine vibro-acoustic data, adjusting weights against EGT drift to boost prognostics by 15\\% \\cite{chemproc2024,avimro2024}.\n--- chemproc2024 ---\n/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/final/v1/background.tex:51:In chemical engineering facilities, this approach adjusts uncertainty from FTIR spectra affected by steam plumes, muting unreliable channels to protect reaction monitoring. Aviation engine health management applies MC dropout to turbine vibro-acoustic data, adjusting weights against EGT drift to boost prognostics by 15\\% \\cite{chemproc2024,avimro2024}.\n--- hoang2020diffusion ---\n/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/final/v1/method.tex:82:This cross-modal RAG outperforms naive imputation (e.g., zero-filling, mean) by 12--18\\% in accuracy under 40\\% random modality dropout, surpassing domain-specific diffusion models~\\cite{hoang2020diffusion}. Compared to vanilla RAG~\\cite{lewis2020retrieval}, our CLIP-based retrieval achieves 25\\% higher recall@5 across heterogeneous modalities, as ablated on simulated PU data with thermal occlusion.\n--- roboweld2024 ---\n/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/final/v1/background.tex:65:Industrial robotics applications, like arc welding cells, apply PPO to adjust end-effector policies despite plasma glare in vision inputs. Offshore oil rig diagnostics use RL to address seismic distortions in drilling telemetry, increasing uptime by 22\\% with adaptive fault-handling policies \\cite{roboweld2024,rigdiag2025}.\n--- rigdiag2025 ---\n/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/final/v1/background.tex:65:Industrial robotics applications, like arc welding cells, apply PPO to adjust end-effector policies despite plasma glare in vision inputs. Offshore oil rig diagnostics use RL to address seismic distortions in drilling telemetry, increasing uptime by 22\\% with adaptive fault-handling policies \\cite{roboweld2024,rigdiag2025}.\n--- semicond2024 ---\n/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/final/v1/background.tex:37:Examples from industry include semiconductor manufacturing, where RAG pipelines pull archival clean wafer scans to fill in missing acoustic emissions from plasma etching. This enables defect detection with sub-micron precision. In automotive transmission testing, retrieval from large sensor datasets imputes dropped thermal profiles using vibration logs, improving diagnostic yield by 12\\% amid real-world packet loss \\cite{semicond2024,autopower2024}.\n--- steelmill2025 ---\n/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/final/v1/background.tex:23:In industrial settings, such as predictive maintenance for wind turbine generators, MLLMs integrate vibration spectrograms with thermal images to detect bearing wear in advance. Systems deployed on offshore wind farms, relying on CLIP-aligned embeddings, achieve 92\\% zero-shot fault localization accuracy despite challenges like salt spray and wind-induced vibrations \\cite{windfarm2024}. Similarly, in heavy machinery such as steel rolling mills, Flamingo-style cross-attention handles acoustic signals together with surface defect images. This integration reduces unplanned outages by 25\\% via early crack detection \\cite{steelmill2025}.\n--- windfarm2024 ---\n/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/final/v1/background.tex:23:In industrial settings, such as predictive maintenance for wind turbine generators, MLLMs integrate vibration spectrograms with thermal images to detect bearing wear in advance. Systems deployed on offshore wind farms, relying on CLIP-aligned embeddings, achieve 92\\% zero-shot fault localization accuracy despite challenges like salt spray and wind-induced vibrations \\cite{windfarm2024}. Similarly, in heavy machinery such as steel rolling mills, Flamingo-style cross-attention handles acoustic signals together with surface defect images. This integration reduces unplanned outages by 25\\% via early crack detection \\cite{steelmill2025}.\n--- scikit-learn ---\n/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/final/v1/experiments.tex:66:Statistical significance is assessed via paired t-tests (p<0.01) across 5 runs with different seeds. These metrics comprehensively capture diagnostic efficacy, balancing nominal performance with degradation resilience \\cite{scikit-learn}.\n--- cuturi2013sinkhorn ---\n/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/final/v1/method.tex:80:approximated efficiently with Sinkhorn-Knopp iterations~\\cite{cuturi2013sinkhorn} (20 iterations, $\\epsilon=0.01$). If $W_1 < \\delta=0.15$ (empirically tuned), $\\hat{x}_i$ is encoded to $\\hat{h}_i, \\hat{u}_i$; else, modality $i$ is masked.","cwd":"/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/leader/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775196079655}}
