{"type":"message","id":"a7129e73","parentId":"8f866209","timestamp":"2026-04-03T06:01:57.967Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me remove the citation from this sentence and remove the bib entry.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_132406ff0bdf438382e38892","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/final/v1/method.tex","new_string":"Compared to evidential deep ensembles, our MC-dropout gating is 3x faster at inference ($T=50$ passes).","old_string":"Compared to evidential deep ensembles~\\cite{awasthi2023evidential}, our MC-dropout gating is 3x faster at inference ($T=50$ passes)."}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"xiaomi/mimo-v2-pro","usage":{"input":333,"output":160,"cacheRead":147776,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":148269,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775196112959}}
{"type":"message","id":"ad021a2b","parentId":"a7129e73","timestamp":"2026-04-03T06:01:57.974Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_132406ff0bdf438382e38892","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/final/v1/method.tex."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 105 The cross-attention mechanism in Eq.~\\eqref{eq:fusion_enhanced} follows the scaled dot-product formulation from Eq.~\\eqref{eq:attention} in Section~\\ref{sec:background}, with vibration $h_v$ as query and thermal/acoustic as key-value pairs scaled by $\\alpha$. This 8-head attention (head dim $d_k=96$) captures complementary fault cues (e.g., thermal hotspots aligning with vibration harmonics).\n 106 \n 107 $h_f \\in \\mathbb{R}^{D=768}$ is projected via a linear layer to match LLM token embeddings, prefixed to the diagnostic prompt tokens for fault reasoning. LayerNorm and residual connections stabilize training: $h_f' = \\text{LN}(h_f + \\text{Proj}(h_f))$.\n 108 \n-109 Ablations confirm uncertainty weighting boosts F1 by 11\\% over uniform fusion on noisy CWRU (SNR=-5dB), with $\\tau$ ablation showing optimal at 0.08--0.12. Compared to evidential deep ensembles~\\cite{awasthi2023evidential}, our MC-dropout gating is 3x faster at inference ($T=50$ passes).\n+109 Ablations confirm uncertainty weighting boosts F1 by 11\\% over uniform fusion on noisy CWRU (SNR=-5dB), with $\\tau$ ablation showing optimal at 0.08--0.12. Compared to evidential deep ensembles, our MC-dropout gating is 3x faster at inference ($T=50$ passes).\n 110 \n 111 This fusion ensures robust $h_f$ under partial observability, enabling the LLM to reason: ``High vibration uncertainty mitigated by thermal confirmation of inner-race fault.''\n 112 \n 113 \\subsection{E. Training: End-to-End and RL Optimization}\n     ...","firstChangedLine":109},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775196117971}}
