{"type":"message","id":"388cdd55","parentId":"1777400f","timestamp":"2026-04-03T06:03:43.360Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_0d07c5203a2a48c68d50be8e","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/final/v1/background.tex:23:Industrial deployments of MLLMs for predictive maintenance have shown promising results, with systems achieving 90\\%+ zero-shot localization accuracy. Similarly, in heavy machinery such as steel rolling mills, Flamingo-style cross-attention handles acoustic signals together with surface defect images. This integration reduces unplanned outages by 25\\% via early crack detection \\cite{steelmill2025}."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":4,"aggregated":"/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/final/v1/background.tex:23:Industrial deployments of MLLMs for predictive maintenance have shown promising results, with systems achieving 90\\%+ zero-shot localization accuracy. Similarly, in heavy machinery such as steel rolling mills, Flamingo-style cross-attention handles acoustic signals together with surface defect images. This integration reduces unplanned outages by 25\\% via early crack detection \\cite{steelmill2025}.","cwd":"/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/leader/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775196223356}}
{"type":"message","id":"447b1f6c","parentId":"388cdd55","timestamp":"2026-04-03T06:03:57.326Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The sed replacement earlier left a \\cite{steelmill2025} in background.tex. Let me fix it.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_03bc94532db14e7998c48eee","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/final/v1/background.tex","new_string":"Industrial deployments of MLLMs for predictive maintenance have shown promising results, with systems achieving 90\\%+ zero-shot localization accuracy. Cross-attention mechanisms effectively fuse acoustic and visual signals for early fault detection.","old_string":"Industrial deployments of MLLMs for predictive maintenance have shown promising results, with systems achieving 90\\%+ zero-shot localization accuracy. Similarly, in heavy machinery such as steel rolling mills, Flamingo-style cross-attention handles acoustic signals together with surface defect images. This integration reduces unplanned outages by 25\\% via early crack detection \\cite{steelmill2025}."}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"xiaomi/mimo-v2-pro","usage":{"input":122775,"output":239,"cacheRead":27904,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":150918,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775196223360}}
{"type":"message","id":"ab26d742","parentId":"447b1f6c","timestamp":"2026-04-03T06:03:57.332Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_03bc94532db14e7998c48eee","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/liaowenjie/.openclaw-multi/shared/paper-project-9/final/v1/background.tex."}],"details":{"diff":"    ...\n 19 \\label{eq:attention}\n 20 \\end{equation}\n 21 where $d_k$ represents the key dimension. This equation relies on dot-product similarity scores $QK^\\top$, scaled by $\\sqrt{d_k}$ to offset the quadratic growth in variance for high-dimensional spaces. Doing so prevents vanishing gradients in softmax and maintains stable information flow across modalities \\cite{vaswani2017attention}. Gated fusion of modalities becomes possible, but the method assumes clean inputs. Consequently, noise in fault spectrograms propagates, causing 15-20\\% drops in accuracy on PHM datasets \\cite{lu2024,hoang2025}. Recent efforts fine-tune MLLMs such as LLaVA on domain-specific data \\cite{llava}, but they often ignore uncertainties specific to individual modalities. This limitation calls for our extensions using RAG and uncertainty awareness.\n 22 \n-23 Industrial deployments of MLLMs for predictive maintenance have shown promising results, with systems achieving 90\\%+ zero-shot localization accuracy. Similarly, in heavy machinery such as steel rolling mills, Flamingo-style cross-attention handles acoustic signals together with surface defect images. This integration reduces unplanned outages by 25\\% via early crack detection \\cite{steelmill2025}.\n+23 Industrial deployments of MLLMs for predictive maintenance have shown promising results, with systems achieving 90\\%+ zero-shot localization accuracy. Cross-attention mechanisms effectively fuse acoustic and visual signals for early fault detection.\n 24 \n 25 \\subsection{B. Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)}\n 26 \\label{subsec:rag}\n 27 \n    ...","firstChangedLine":23},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775196237328}}
